The fried chicken was perfect....good seasoning and very juicy. Beignets were okay just a little too dense for me, as I was expecting a lighter/fluffier texture. Cute restaurant, nice decor. Next time I think I'll try something else on the menu maybe the eggs benedict.

Dined here for dinner before going to the theater last night. We started with crawfish beignets, oysters casino and Tchoupitoulas oysters. OMG OMG these oysters were super flavorful and the reason that we will be back, however the beignet was just ok, lacked filling in the center. My husband had the catfish and I went for the shrimp and grits and all I can say is that it was made with love ! He had a beer and I a glass of wine which i wish was in a glass with a stem being it was chilled. Service was nice and gave good suggestions!

Coming from Texas, good food is a non-negotiable whenever I visit somewhere. My family and I are visiting for a family reunion and vacation and a friend of mine highly recommended Brenda's. It. Did. Not. Disappoint. I got the pasta orleans with shrimp, crawfish, mussels, and fusilli. It was fantastic! It didn't come with garlic bread so I asked for some toasted sourdough (staple for SF) but it was better with the spiced strawberry jam than the actual pasta. My wife got the shrimp pot pie and green salad which both were awesome. It had a cheesy top than just a typical biscuit/dough which added to the flavor. If you get the beignets, get the sampler. You can't mix and match but you won't have to. The surprisingly the crawfish beignet may have been my favorite tied with the apple pie one. Our kids split the BFC which has 2 pieces of chicken and fries. This is great for someone who wants something safer or a quick lunch. The food came out fast which was concerning at first but the quality was top notch. The guava mimosa was the only thing we could do without. Looking to go again before we go back to Texas!

Wow. The food here is unmatchable. Came here for brunch on a Saturday and did not regret it! The wait was about 30-40 min as to be expected but the food came out pretty fast and was DELICIOUS. The andouille sausage omelette was to die for and even their potatoes were delicious. The food was well seasoned and just the right touch of spiciness. Will be back!!

    Coming from Texas, good food is a non-negotiable whenever I visit somewhere. My family and I are visiting for a family reunion and vacation and a friend of mine highly recommended Brenda's. It. Did. Not. Disappoint.

    I got the pasta orleans with shrimp, crawfish, mussels, and fusilli. It was fantastic! It didn't come with garlic bread so I asked for some toasted sourdough (staple for SF) but it was better with the spiced strawberry jam than the actual pasta.

    My wife got the shrimp pot pie and green salad which both were awesome. It had a cheesy top than just a typical biscuit/dough which added to the flavor.

    If you get the beignets, get the sampler. You can't mix and match but you won't have to. The surprisingly the crawfish beignet may have been my favorite tied with the apple pie one.

    Our kids split the BFC which has 2 pieces of chicken and fries. This is great for someone who wants something safer or a quick lunch.

    The food came out fast which was concerning at first but the quality was top notch. The guava mimosa was the only thing we could do without.

    Looking to go again before we go back to Texas!

    11/28/2018

    2 photos

    Came for the beignets, stayed for the jam. Another check off my SF food bucket list (I've seen Brenda's all over Buzzfeed and IG).

    My friend and I almost didn't come here for fear of a long wait, but it was only about 30 minutes, and I am so glad we chose to eat here.

    Their Sunday dinner service is a little different than most days-it's called Sunday Supper where they serve their brunch menu and select dinner items. We sort of wanted the etouffe (which wasn't offered) but ended up getting the fried chicken! They also have live music on Sunday until 8, I believe-that was cool!

    BFC ($18.50): RECOMMEND! I usually peel off the chicken skin because it's fatty, but this time I just went for it and bit the whole thing. The skin was crispy and flavorful and the chicken was tender! The collard greens were good, but not my favorite. The biscuit was so fluffy, milky, and buttery! And the jam might have been the best part. It was so fresh and addicting. We had to ask for more to put on our biscuit-I could literally eat it by the spoonful (it's that good)! They sell it for about $10 a jar.

    Beignet Flight ($12): So $3 each? That's a pretty good price. You get one of each-I love the flight concept popping up everywhere because you get a little taste of everything!

    Plain: not really necessary once you try the other beignets-just more dough.

    Ghiradelli Chocolate: Did you think it'd be filled with anything BUT ghiradelli? We're in San Francisco people! There's no shortage of chocolate filling in this one-rich and decadent!

    Granny Smith Apple: a tad bland, but I liked the warmth and spices.

    Crawfish: THE BEST! Spiced with cayenne, scallions, and cheddar. Make sure to video a cheese pull with this one-ours was pretty epic! The crawfish was tender and tasted like shrimp to me (I've never had crawfish before). It was seasoned well.

    We shared these two dishes and it filled us up well!

    Service was ok, they didn't check up on us often and we ran out of water and jam. We asked for a recommendation between BFC and the po'boy and the watiress said the BFC which was a great choice! The food came out pretty quick, too!

    I am definitely coming back here for brunch (although maybe Sunday Supper is a better idea because there's less of a crowd and they still serve breakfast items) or dinner!
